# Wanfa Standard Ops Project Goals

This file records the project-level implementation target for Codex sessions in this repository.

## Current North Star

Build one unified customer-service conversation system across website, WeChat Customer Service, and WeCom, reusing the same Conversation, Message, assignment, AI decision, RAG, and handoff model. Do not create separate channel-specific business logic or parallel status systems.

## Stage 1: Fixed Runtime

Goal: Stop losing time to changing ports, database names, and script URLs.

Fixed runtime values:
- Development backend: `http://127.0.0.1:8000`
- Docker database container: `deploy-postgres-1`
- Website plugin test page: use only one fixed page for website-plugin testing
- Website widget script: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/Web/js/customer-widget.js`
- Widget `apiBase`: `http://127.0.0.1:8000`

Acceptance:
- `GET /health` works.
- Website sends `你好`, and the backend public widget message API returns `201`.
- The customer widget can poll and display the AI reply.

## Stage 2: Hard Three-Column Conversation Ownership

Goal: Make it obvious to customer-service staff who owns each conversation.

Status definitions must stay unchanged:
- `bot_visiting`: AI is serving the visitor; shown in `访问中`.
- `queued_for_me`: assigned to the current agent but not claimed; shown in `排队中`.
- `assigned_to_me`: claimed by the current agent; shown in `我的对话`.

Requirements:
- Conversation lists must show only the current tenant/company data.
- `排队中` only shows conversations assigned to the current agent.
- `我的对话` only shows conversations claimed by the current agent.
- `访问中` shows conversations currently handled by AI.
- Clicking `接起` must call `POST /api/conversations/{id}/claim`.

Acceptance:
- After an AI auto reply, the conversation stays in `访问中`.
- After AI handoff to human, the conversation enters `排队中`.
- After the agent claims it, the conversation enters `我的对话`.
- After close, the conversation disappears from all three columns.

## Stage 3: Knowledge Feeding To RAG Loop

Goal: Customer-service staff can feed knowledge, AI can answer from that knowledge, and AI does not invent answers when knowledge is missing.

Requirements:
- Keep the manual customer-service upload/manual knowledge-entry path.
- Knowledge flow must cover: clean, chunk, embed, retrieve, recall, rerank, generate final answer.
- Product/business consultation must cite matched knowledge.
- If there is no knowledge hit, create a knowledge gap and do not auto-send an invented answer.
- Knowledge gaps must be visible in the backend/workbench so staff can later fill them.

Acceptance:
- Feed one knowledge item: `营业时间是 9:00-18:00`.
- Customer asks `你们几点上班`, and AI can answer with that knowledge.
- Customer asks something absent from the knowledge base; AI does not invent an answer, and the conversation enters `排队中` / knowledge gap.

## Stage 4: AI Handoff Rules

Goal: AI knows when to stop and call a human.

Handoff conditions:
- Complaint
- Abnormal emotion
- Sensitive content
- Prompt injection
- No knowledge hit
- Low confidence
- Model failure
- External send failure
- Customer explicitly asks for a human agent

Requirements:
- Generate calming handoff copy when handing off, but do not auto-send complaint-related copy by default.
- Create a human task.
- Assign it to an agent.
- Conversation enters `queued_for_me`.
- Workbench shows the AI handoff reason.

Acceptance:
- Customer says `我要投诉`, and the conversation enters `排队中`.
- Customer says `转人工`, and the conversation enters `排队中`.
- Customer asks a no-knowledge question, and the conversation enters `排队中`.
- Workbench shows the handoff reason.

## Stage 5: Human Reply Loop

Goal: Agents can actually complete the customer-service flow.

Requirements:
- Claim button.
- Agent sends message.
- Website widget polling displays the agent reply.
- Agent closes conversation.
- Customer side shows the conversation ended.
- Customer can choose to continue chatting and reopen a new conversation.

Acceptance:
- Agent claims conversation.
- Agent replies `您好，我来帮您处理`.
- Customer website window sees the reply.
- Agent closes the conversation.
- Customer side sees the conversation ended.

## Stage 6: WeChat Customer Service Channel

Goal: Copy the already working website main flow into WeChat Customer Service.

Requirements:
- WeChat Customer Service inbound webhook.
- WeChat Customer Service outbound sender.
- Reuse the same AI decision, RAG, handoff, and three-column status model.
- Do not build separate WeChat-specific business logic.

Acceptance:
- WeChat customer message enters `访问中`.
- If AI can reply, it sends through the WeChat Customer Service API.
- On handoff, the conversation enters `排队中`.
- After an agent claims it, the manual reply can be sent back to the WeChat customer.

## Stage 7: WeCom Custom App Channel

Goal: Add WeCom custom app as a third channel while still reusing the unified conversation model.

Requirements:
- First decide whether WeCom custom app is a customer entry channel or an internal support/collaboration tool.
- If it is a customer entry channel, route it through channel inbound.
- If it is for internal support notifications/collaboration, do not confuse it with customer conversation entry.
- Reuse unified Conversation, Message, assignment, and AI decision logic.

Acceptance:
- WeCom message can create the same kind of Conversation.
- AI/manual logic does not fork.
- There is no separate `WeCom status system` beside the website status system.

## Operating Notes

- Prefer fixing the actual runtime drift over adding compatibility branches.
- Keep backend development address fixed at `http://127.0.0.1:8000`.
- Keep website-widget script and widget `apiBase` aligned with `http://127.0.0.1:8000`.
- Keep three-column status names exact: `bot_visiting`, `queued_for_me`, `assigned_to_me`.
- When implementing new channels, reuse the existing conversation lifecycle instead of inventing a channel-specific lifecycle.
